    "summary": "I like to use my results-driven, creative mindset and strong analytical skills to solve multidisciplinary problems. The chemistry and sustainability of historical and industrial paints are my primary interests. I believe that combining people and knowledge from different backgrounds is the key to innovation.\n\nMY MISSION\n \u25a0 to actively contributes to a more sustainable future;\n \u25a0 to use my knowledge and skills in an ambitious, interdisciplinary environment;\n \u25a0 to communicate about my work to a broad audience through education, talks, journalism and art.\n\nMY ACHIEVEMENTS\n\u25a0 obtained a PhD about the chemistry of oil paint at the UvA and the Rijksmuseum;\n\u25a0 published 10 papers in peer-reviewed journals;\n\u25a0 presented at numerous multidisciplinary scientific conferences;\n\u25a0 graduated cum laude as a Master of Science in Chemistry (2014);\n\u25a0 received an interdisciplinary bachelor (BSc) in natural and social sciences, majoring in chemistry  (2012).\n\nMY EXPERTISE\n \u25a0 strong analytic, creative and numerical insight;\n \u25a0 a trained interdisciplinary mindset, integrating natural sciences and social sciences;\n \u25a0 strong writing and oral communication skills in Dutch and English;\n \u25a0 an ambition to learn and constantly improve myself.\n\n\nPlease feel free to contact me.",
