                    "description": "PhD thesis: 'A molecular perspective on the cleaning of paintings'\n\nQuestions that I dealt with in this project are: \n\n\u2022 Can the exposure of oil paint to solvents trigger reactions inside the paint?\n\u2022 How do reactions inside the polymeric binding medium depend on varying environmental conditions?\n\u2022 How do modern cleaning materials, such as hydrogels or microfibre tissues, compare to traditional cleaning methods in terms of solvent transport inside the paint?\n\u2022 How do we develop a reliable assessment of the risks involved in solvent-based cleaning treatments?\n\nDue to the inherent multidisciplinary nature of these questions, the use of a range of analytical techniques is required.  In my project, I combine sub-disciplines of chemistry such as inorganic-, organic-, polymer-, analytical chemistry and spectroscopy.",
